The paper discusses the generalization properties of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a statistical mechanics approach to understanding these properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also touches on the behavior of learning algorithms, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory), although these are less likely sub-categories.
